    <h2>Magento Product Feeds – Make Your Products Highly Visible to Shoppers</h2>
    <p>Have you noticed when you do an online search for a product, buying options appear right on the search results page, before you even go to a website?&nbsp;By setting up your&nbsp;product feed on&nbsp;<a href="https://www.google.com/shopping?hl=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Shopping</a>, <a href="http://www.shopzilla.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Shopzilla</a>&nbsp;and other comparison shopping channels, your products can appear to shoppers in this way.<strong>&nbsp;</strong>Our team&nbsp;can:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Align your website with top shopping channels</li>
        <li>Set up and&nbsp;manage&nbsp;your product feeds in comparison shopping channels</li>
        <li>Strategically align actions with your sales goals and seasonal promotions</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Integrate Your Magento Website with Amazon</h2>
    <p>Your Magento eCommerce website (property that you own on the Internet), can be integrated with the <a href="http://www.amazon.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Amazon</a> behemoth, to maximize sales opportunities and expedite processes for you. Options include:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Orders placed on&nbsp;your website are fulfilled by Amazon (FBA); inventory levels are synchronized to adjust accordingly</li>
        <li>Your store integrates with Amazon with you handling fulfillment</li>
    </ul>
